description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Come and join City Community Hospital nursing team to make a real difference!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for Registered Nurses who have experience from an acute or community setting to join our nurturing and supportive team, being led by a new dynamic leadership team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be highly enthusiastic and motivated with a passion to care for older patients who may have a complexity of health needs providing sub-acute and rehabilitation recovery, all within a supportive environment where our nurses have the ability to expand their core skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will posse excellent communication skills, a positive attitude with a strong commitment to learn within our wonderful nurse-lead team, working alongside other Healthcare Professionals. In return, we can offer you a great induction and clinical supervision programme and in-house training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At City Community Hospital, we are co-located with the Fulbrook Centre in the lovely setting of Headington in Oxford with excellent bus services and local shops nearby.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are looking to be part of a new, exciting team and enjoy a challenge, then we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CommunityHospitalRecruitment@oxfordhealth.nhs.uk or Christine Hayden (Ward Manager) on 01865 902888.&lt;/p&gt;
